rComments: arguably one of my favorite prof. His delivery is tough but extremely straightforward - such that he sets VERY clear expectations to succeed in this course. Just follow the steps. Rick somehow has the ability to explain and communicate intricate tax details all so concisely. As an international student, i found his lectures extremely helpful

The worst prof ever... told a student the second week of class that she was going to fail the course since she can't put in 3-4 hours of focused studying every single day. Also, just because Rick has worked in taxes and owned his own tax business, doesn't give him the right to belittle students and be as harsh on his testing.

The professor is unwilling to make things easy for you. The class is entirely self-taught and he likes to keep it that way. Screencasts glaze over the content at most but are more often telling you what to do. Synch sessions are just re-iterating how hard the class is, he doesn't do any active teaching. Ask a question? He'll tell u to look it up.

rComments: His videos just keep saying CPA is tough, it's important, you need to work hard but doesn't teach anything. He asked us to practice the questions in the book, but the content of the exam was different from that in the book. What's the use of this kind of teacher staying in school?

This prof is an obstacle to your success in accounting. He makes the difficult materials ten times harder than it is supposed to be, and there is no way that you will do well in this class because you don't have any resources to teach yourself. Don't feel bad about yourself because u r not Ben Affleck from The Accountant, who is a genius accountant
will never take a course from this professor using respondus and the questions are hard furthermore, u cant go back to the question u have done

Rick is clearly a nice person but I didn't enjoy his class at all. He put too much emphasis on the students' studying habits and not enough on the actual material. If he talked more about the course material the time spent in his class would have been far more enjoyable.

Very nice guy, but doesnt understand that students have 4 other classes, a job and a social life! he thinks tax is the only class we have! read the txt book and do the problems and maybe youll be fine... no need to go to class!
